{
    "info": {
        "name": "Doctorna API v2 (Complete Integration)",
        "description": "\n# Doctorna API v2 (Complete Integration)\n\nWelcome to the **Doctorna API**! This collection is ready-to-use for testing all modules: Authentication, Doctors, Appointments, Patients, and Specialities.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udea6 How to Use This Collection\n\n### 1. Set Your Base URL\nGo to the **Variables** tab of this collection. Ensure the `base_url` variable correctly points to your local environment (e.g., `http://localhost/threedos-backend/tasks/task-06/doctorna/routes`).\n\n### 2. Login to Get Your Tokens\n1. Open the **1. Authentication** folder.\n2. Run **Register (Public)** to create an Admin user (change `role` to `admin` in the body) and a standard User (role `user`).\n3. Run **Login (Public)** with those credentials.\n4. **Important:** Copy the `token` from the login response.\n5. Go to the collection's **Variables** tab and paste it into:\n   - `admin_token` (if you logged in as Admin)\n   - `user_token` (if you logged in as User)\n\n### 3. Authorization is Automatic\nYou do not need to paste your token into every request! We have configured this collection to automatically use `{{admin_token}}` or `{{user_token}}` depending on what permission the endpoint requires.\n\n### 4. Dynamic Filtering (X-Request-Type)\nFor endpoints like **Filter Doctors**, notice that we use the `X-Request-Type: filter` Header. This tells the server to actively look at your Query Parameters (`?gender=female&rank=specialist`) and apply them dynamically to the database.\n\n---\n\n## \ud83d\udd10 Role Definitions\n- **Public**: No token required (e.g., Browsing Doctors, Specialities, Logging in).\n- **User**: Requires `{{user_token}}`. Can only access their own Appointments and book new ones.\n- **Admin**: Requires `{{admin_token}}`. Has global access to Create, Update, Delete, and view all system records.\n",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "1. Authentication",
            "description": "Endpoints for user registration, login, and password recovery.",
            "item": [
                {
                    "name": "Register (Public)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
                        "body": {
                            "mode": "raw",
                            "raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Ahmed User\",\n    \"email\": \"ahmed@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"StrongPass123!\",\n    \"age\": 25,\n    \"gender\": \"male\",\n    \"phone\": \"01012345678\",\n    \"role\": \"user\"\n}",
                            "options": {
                                "raw": {
                                    "language": "json"
                                }
                            }
                        },
                        "url": {
                            "raw": "{{base_url}}/AuthRoute.php/auth/register",
                            "host": [
                                "{{base_url}}"
                            ],
                            "path": [
                                "AuthRoute.php",
                                "auth",
                                "register"
                            ]
                        },
                        "description": "Register a new user. Role must be 'user'. Password requires upper, lower, number, and special char."
                    }
                },
                {
                    "name": "Login (Public)",
                    "request": {
                        "method": "POST",
                        "header": [],
